6.00	Atherton%2C_Greater_Manchester	Atherton, Greater Manchester	Atherton (pop. 20,300) is a town within the Metropolitan Borough of Wigan, in Greater Manchester, England, historically a part of Lancashire. It is 5 miles (8.0 km) east of Wigan, 2 miles (3.2 km) north-northeast of Leigh, and 10.7 miles (17.2 km) northwest of Manchester. For about 300 years from the 17th century Atherton was referred to as Chowbent, which was frequently shortened to Bent, the town's old nickname.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c4/Market_Street%2C_Atherton.jpg/240px-Market_Street%2C_Atherton.jpg
